Open this because [old issue](https://github.com/mistralai/platform-docs-public/issues/263#issue-3142521178) is closed being unresolved

@jean-malo

Unfortunately your [example](https://github.com/mistralai/platform-docs-public/issues/263#issuecomment-2969389887) does not work for me. Here's the JSON I send:

```json
{
  "model": "mistral-ocr-latest",
  "include_image_base64": true,
  "document": {
    "type": "image_url",
    "image_url": "data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQEASABIAAD/2wBDAAQDAwQDAwQEAwQFBAQFBgoH...+208664 more"
  }
}
```

Here's the response Mistral OCR API request failed with status 400:


```json
{"object":"error","message":"Failed to fetch document","type":"invalid_request_error"}
```

In your OpenAPI specification you specify `msg` in a `ValidationError` as `string`:
https://github.com/mistralai/platform-docs-public/blob/c986c74ad75ce7f2a3ae619d5116e52d9f6f87e5/openapi.yaml#L1095-L1097

However, testing a lot of invalid requests to your `https://api.mistral.ai/v1/chat/completions` endpoint shows that `msg` can be also (or is always?) an array:

```json
"message": {
  "detail": [
    {
      "type": "float_type",
      "loc": [
        "body",
        "top_p"
      ],
      "msg": "Input should be a valid number",
      "input": null
    }
  ]
}, ...
```

👋, this fix is for a small typo in [Guardrailing section](https://docs.mistral.ai/capabilities/guardrailing/) for the Javascript library. 

```diff
const chatResponse = await client.chat(
    model: 'mistral-large-latest',
    messages: [{role: 'user', content: 'What is the best French cheese?'}],
-   safe_prompt: true
+   safePrompt: true
);
```
